Barcelona vs Real Madrid: Livescore from El Clasico clash in LaLiga Barcelona and Real Madrid go into Wednesday’s El Clasico game joint top of LaLiga. The champions drew 2-2 at Athletic Bilbao on Saturday, while Los Blancos failed to overtake them following a 1-1 draw with Valencia. This game at the Camp Nou was postponed from its original date because of riots, but will now see both rivals seek to open a gap. Kick-off is 9pm West African time. Barcelona XI: Ter Stegen, Piqué, Lenglet, Jordi Alba, Semedo, S. Roberto, Rakitić, De Jong, Messi, Griezmann, Suárez. Real Madrid XI: Courtois, Ramos, Varane, Mendy, Carvajal, Kroos, Casemiro, Valverde, Isco, Bale, Benzema. Wednesday, December 18
